<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Fox" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Fox,</orth> 1) the animal Vulpes: <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.3.174" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 3, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 3.85" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 3.85" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 85</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 3.85" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 85</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.237" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 237</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.237" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 237</bibl> <bibl n="shak. aww 3.6.111" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 6, 111</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.2.9" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 2, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.256" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 256</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.7.25" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 7, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.340" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 340</bibl> (fem.). <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.96" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 96</bibl>. Opposed to the lamb as its natural enemy: <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.97" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. IV, 4, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 5.300" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 300</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.55" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.55" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 55</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tro 3.2.200" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 2, 200</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.332" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 332</bibl>. <cit><quote>will you eat no grapes, my royal f.?</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.1.73" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 1, 73</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>fire us hence like --es,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 23</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>hide f., and all after,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 4.2.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 2, 33</bibl></cit> (a sport of children). <cit><quote>Sowter will cry upon't for all this, though it be as rank as a f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 2.5.136" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 5, 136</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to wake a wolf is as bad as to smell a f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.176" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 176</bibl></cit>. Emblem of ingratitude: <cit><quote>now, you she --es,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.6.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 6, 24</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.340" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 340</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.7.28" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 7, 28</bibl>. Of cunning: <bibl n="shak. ven 675" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 675</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.234" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 234</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.3.129" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 3, 129</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.176" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 176</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.331" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 331</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.3.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 3, 40</bibl>. Hence == a cunning fellow: <bibl n="shak. shr 2.405" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 405</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.158" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 158</bibl>.<lb />2) a sword: <cit><quote>thou diest on point of f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.4.9" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 4, 9</bibl></cit> (Pistol's speech. The figure of a fox was frequently engraved on blades).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>